## Question

Which source code path is actually used for sensor voting / estimator selection — `VotedSensorsUpdate` (in `src/modules/sensors/`) or `EKF2Selector` (in `src/modules/ekf2/`)? Are both compiled? Are both active at runtime?

## Short answer

**Both are compiled into the build and both can run.** They are not competing replacements; they are two voting layers at different stages of the pipeline. Which one's output the flight controller actually consumes is gated at runtime by the `SENS_IMU_MODE` parameter.

---

## Source locations

| Class | Source files |
|---|---|
| `VotedSensorsUpdate` | `src/modules/sensors/voted_sensors_update.h`, `voted_sensors_update.cpp` |
| `EKF2Selector` | `src/modules/ekf2/EKF2Selector.hpp`, `EKF2Selector.cpp` |

Both are listed in their respective module `CMakeLists.txt`. The `sensors` module is enabled by default (`CONFIG_MODULES_SENSORS=y`, e.g. `boards/px4/sitl/default.px4board:44`). The `EKF2Selector` is built only when `CONFIG_EKF2_MULTI_INSTANCE` is set in `src/modules/ekf2/Kconfig` — that flag is on by default unless the board declares `CONSTRAINED_MEMORY` / `CONSTRAINED_FLASH`.

