## What each one publishes

### VotedSensorsUpdate (instantiated unconditionally inside the `Sensors` module)

- Directly publishes uORB topics:
  - `sensor_selection` — device IDs of the selected best accel/gyro
  - `sensors_status_imu` — per-instance health, inconsistency metrics, priorities
- Populates the `sensor_combined` struct; the parent `Sensors` module publishes it:
  - `src/modules/sensors/sensors.cpp:615` — `_voted_sensors_update.sensorsPoll(_sensor_combined)`
  - `src/modules/sensors/sensors.cpp:620` — `_sensor_pub.publish(_sensor_combined)`
- Input: per-instance `vehicle_imu[0..N]` topics produced by `VehicleIMU` workers.

### EKF2Selector (only constructed when `_multi_mode == true`)

- Publishes the canonical "fused" flight-controller topics:
  - `vehicle_attitude`
  - `vehicle_local_position`
  - `vehicle_global_position`
  - `vehicle_odometry`
  - `wind`
  - `estimator_selector_status` (selector's own health/metadata)
  - `sensor_selection` (re-published with the selected EKF2 instance's sensor IDs)
- Subscribes to per-instance estimator outputs from each EKF2 replica:
  - `estimator_attitude[i]`, `estimator_local_position[i]`, `estimator_global_position[i]`, `estimator_odometry[i]`, `estimator_wind[i]`, `estimator_status[i]`
- Picks the healthiest instance by combined test ratio (velocity / position / height errors) with ~10s hysteresis between switches unless a hard fault is detected.

